# Driver API Centre (DAC) configuration

config DRIVER_API_CENTRE
	bool "Driver API Centre — sandbox and validate all drivers"
	depends on RUST
	select FW_HEALTH
	help
	  The Driver API Centre (DAC) provides:
	    - Per-driver sandboxing with fault isolation and recovery
	    - API key validation for every kernel call a driver makes
	    - Unified per-driver ring-buffer logging via sysfs
	    - Crash detection via fw_health heartbeat monitoring
	    - Transparent wrapping of all existing drivers (no source changes)

	  When a driver crashes, DAC prevents it from making further API
	  calls, logs the fault, and can trigger automatic recovery.

	  If unsure, say N.

config DAC_DEBUG
	bool "DAC debugging — log every API call"
	depends on DRIVER_API_CENTRE
	help
	  Logs every API call through the DAC gateway.  Very verbose.

config DAC_LEGACY_RTLWIFI
	bool "Rewrite Realtek rtlwifi in Rust with native DAC API"
	depends on DRIVER_API_CENTRE
	help
	  Replaces the legacy C rtlwifi driver (508K lines, highest
	  crash rate) with a Rust implementation using DAC for all
	  DMA/PCI/MMIO/log calls.
